github_projects_integration.instructions:
1. Create Epic issue using Feature Epic template: gh issue create --repo {REPO} --title "[EPIC] {TITLE}" --template feature-epic.yml --body "{PRD_CONTENT}" --label "epic,needs-refinement,AAFD-stage:PRD"
2. Add to GitHub Projects: gh project item-add {PROJECT_NUMBER} --owner {OWNER} --url {ISSUE_URL}
3. Set custom fields: - Feature Type: Epic - AAFD Stage: PRD - Priority: {HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW based on business impact} - AI Context Status: Fresh - Technical Domain: {Frontend/Backend/Database/AI/DevOps} - Milestone: {RELEASE_MILESTONE}
4. Move to Planning Board "PRD" column
5. Store PRD context: - Save to: .claude/build/4-output/{epic-name}/1-prd/prd-content.md - Create context file: .claude/build/4-output/contexts/epics/epic-{epic-id}/prd.md
6. Next phase preparation: - Epic ready for technical chunking (Phase 2) - Context files prepared for Claude Code sessions
